sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM platforms 
WHERE platform_id = 0;

SELECT platform_id, COUNT(game_id) AS game_count
FROM game_platforms
GROUP BY platform_id;

SELECT g.game_name
FROM games g
WHERE g.rating >= 70;

external_knowledge:
'action-packed vessels' refers to games in the 'Action' genre;
'curious eyes' refers to unique users who have viewed the game;
'sea level of their ratings' is a metaphorical way of referring to the average ratings of the games.
